      "deletions": 1,
      "changes": 2,
      "blob_url": "https://github.com/flashinfer-ai/flashinfer/blob/8f155573621f7f795803ab535ea306b39f03210e/benchmarks%2FREADME.md",
      "raw_url": "https://github.com/flashinfer-ai/flashinfer/raw/8f155573621f7f795803ab535ea306b39f03210e/benchmarks%2FREADME.md",
      "contents_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/flashinfer-ai/flashinfer/contents/benchmarks%2FREADME.md?ref=8f155573621f7f795803ab535ea306b39f03210e",
      "patch": "@@ -184,7 +184,7 @@ The output CSV will contain detailed metrics including:\n | `--verbose`, `-v`        | Print additional information (can be used multiple times for more verbosity, e.g. `-vv`)                   |\n | `--case_tag`              | Optional tag for the test case, useful for annotating or filtering results in the output CSV.              |\n | `--generate_repro_command`| If set, prints a reproducer command for the test case and stores it in the output CSV.                     |\n-| `--backends`             | Space-separated list of backends to test, e.g. fa2, fa2_tc, fa3, cudnn, cudnn-native, cutlass, trtllm, trtllm-gen, trtllm-native, cublas|\n+| `--backends`             | Space-separated list of backends to test, e.g. fa2, fa2_tc, fa3, auto, cudnn, cudnn-native, cutlass, trtllm, trtllm-gen, trtllm-native, cublas. (`auto` currently supported for `BatchDecodeWithPagedKVCacheWrapper` and `BatchPrefillWithPagedKVCacheWrapper`.)|\n \n ### Attention Flags\n | Flag                     | Description                                                                                                 |"
    },
    {
      "sha": "9b3e8cb20617d859977024ed750129f46b903118",
      "filename": "benchmarks/routines/attention.py",
      "status": "modified",
